posts.name: Aiden Powers
posts.cooked: From venue match result to FIRST API match breakdown, has anyone measured how long this takes?
Never measured it, but I've noticed some inconsistencies. Sometimes it works very quickly, while other times it falls a few matches behind.

posts.name: Ty Galle
posts.cooked: some inconsistency sometimes it was pretty fast sometimes it was a few matches behind Is it roughly the same for each given event Or does it fluctuate a lot? So in your experience do you find that the response time or lag between events is consistent across different events or does it vary significantly

posts.name: Peter Cooper Jr.
posts.cooked: All right, so if everything is running smoothly—like the venue’s internet connection, the Field Management System (FMS), and the FIRST Robotics Competition (FRC) backend—then the scores should appear on the big screens at the same time they’re posted. However, there’s no guarantee, although sometimes the FRC backend might lag before syncing up again.

posts.name: Austin Schweikert
posts.cooked: Is it not pretty instantaneous? I've scanned the QR code that they show on the match results screens a few times and usually can see the entire breakdown, IIRc.

posts.name: Stephen Ostermiller
posts.cooked: This season, it has been consistently under a couple of minutes. I haven't been measuring the seconds; a couple of minutes is good enough for my purposes. That is a big improvement from last year. Last year, it was common for events to stop uploading. The data would often be delayed by hours. Sometimes, it wouldn't become available in the API until after the event was over.

posts.name: Stephen Ostermiller
posts.cooked: Extremely Important: First, announced at Week 0 that they had been working on improving the upload method as well as the backup upload methods. They expected API data to become available quickly after matches this season. Their improvements seemed to have worked really well. I didn’t notice a single major delay the entire season. A+++ to First for their work getting data from the Field Management System to the API.

posts.name: alst
posts.cooked: Also mentioned on the FRC blog: Notes Heading Into Week 1.
Ohh amazing stopped using some of the data from the API because of the delays. Great to hear that it's better now.
